  <title>Forces</title>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="PopupTable" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Forces</text> is the collective term we use for kinematic-force calculations and display.</para>
          <list id="23" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Popup Box" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Popup Box">Force at Pin-Joints and Slide-Joints </li>
          </list>
          <list id="24" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Popup Box" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Popup Box">Drive Torque</li>
            <li styleclass="Popup Box">Drive Force</li>
            <li styleclass="Popup Box">Cam Contact Force</li>
            <li styleclass="Popup Box">Spring Force</li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Kinetostatic Forces</text> are those forces and reaction forces in parts and at joints that are a consequence of their movement.</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">We tend to use the terms:</para>
          <list id="25" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Popup Box" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Drive Torque</text><text style="font-style:italic;">&#32;</text>for the &apos;moment&apos; a Rotary Motor must provide to the mechanism</li>
            <li styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Drive Force</text> for the &apos;linear force&apos; a Linear Motor must provide to the mechanism</li>
          </list>
        </td>
      </tr>
